-- Symrise Takes Long-Term Loan of $175 Million, to Use Funds for Refinancing
-- B y   M i k e   G a v i n
-- 2010-10-13T05:33:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-13/symrise-takes-long-term-loan-of-175-million-to-use-funds-for-refinancing.html
Symrise AG has agreed to a senior
term note of $175 million with Prudential Investment Management
Inc. as part of its refinancing concept. The note has a duration
of 10 years with a coupon of 170 basis points above the 10-year
U.S. Treasury bond, Symrise said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Mike Gavin at 
 mgavin2@bloomberg.net  